  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Nicias, from Miletus, physician and poet, 3rd cent. B.C.,
    fellow pupil of Erasistratus and friend of Theocritus. Besides an epigram (8 Gow) to a statue erected
    by N. in honour of Asclepius, Theocritus dedicated eidyllia 11 and 13 to N., and 28 to N.'s wife. N. 
    responded to Theocr. 11 with a poem (SH 566). We also have eight four-line epigrams by N. (not by him: Anth.
    Pal. 11.398)...."</mads:note>
